-- Storebrand faces $2.1 bln reserve increase requirement
-- 
-- Fri Mar 28, 2014 03:08AM EDT
-- None



OSLO, March 28 (Reuters) - Norwegian insurer Storebrand <STB.OL> faces a 12.5 billion crown ($2.1 billion) reserve strengthening requirement due to the government's new mortality assumptions, slightly less than the 12.7 billion seen earlier, it said on Friday.

